text:
I am having a problem with getting my XML Schema validation to work properly 
when a element or attributte name is invalid in the instance document.

In my parse method I have implemented the SAX ErrorHandler...  

class ReportParserError implements org.xml.sax.ErrorHandler
{
    public void warning(org.xml.sax.SAXParseException e) {
       System.err.println("Warning From DOM Parser: " + e.getMessage());	
    }

    public void error(org.xml.sax.SAXParseException e) {		
	System.err.println("ERROR: " + e.getMessage());
    }

    public void fatalError(org.xml.sax.SAXParseException e) {	
	System.err.println("FATAL ERROR: " + e.getMessage());
    }
}

parser.setErrorHandler(new ReportParserError());
// tell the parser to enforce validation
parser.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/validation/schema", true);


This works for "well-formed" documents.  Errors are generated just fine when 
the instance document is not well-formed.  However, when I intentionally change 
a name of an attributte or element that is not in my schema, the validation 
does not report any errors.  Also, any date type checking does not seem to be 
validated also.

I have tried this with the latest version of XERCES 1.3.
My schema is implemented using the either the 04/2000 or 10/2000 spec.
